metricsRuleDefinitions.alertText: Batch taking more time to process

configDefinitions.name: retryAttempts
configDefinitions.description: Max no of retries. To retry indefinitely, use -1. The wait time between retries starts at 15 seconds and doubles until reaching 5 minutes.
configDefinitions.label: Retry Attempts

configDefinitions.name: memoryLimit
configDefinitions.description: Maximum amount of memory the pipeline can use. Configure in relationship to the SDC Java heap size. The default is 650 and a value of 0 or less disables the limit.
configDefinitions.label: Max Pipeline Memory (MB)

configDefinitions.name: memoryLimitExceeded
configDefinitions.description: Behavior when the pipeline exceeds the memory limit. Tip: Configure an alert to indicate when the memory use approaches the limit.
configDefinitions.label: On Memory Exceeded

configDefinitions.name: notifyOnStates
configDefinitions.description: Notifies via email when pipeline gets to the specified states
configDefinitions.label: Notify on Pipeline State Changes

configDefinitions.name: emailIDs
configDefinitions.description: Email Addresses
configDefinitions.label: Email IDs

configDefinitions.name: clusterSlaveJavaOpts
configDefinitions.description: Add properties as needed. Changes to default settings are not recommended.
configDefinitions.label: Worker Java Options

configDefinitions.name: clusterLauncherEnv
configDefinitions.description: Sets additional environment variables for the cluster launcher
configDefinitions.label: Launcher ENV

configDefinitions.name: mesosDispatcherURL
configDefinitions.description: URL for service which launches Mesos framework
configDefinitions.label: Mesos Dispatcher URL

configDefinitions.name: hdfsS3ConfDir
configDefinitions.description: An SDC resource directory or symbolic link with HDFS/S3 configuration files core-site.xml and hdfs-site.xml
configDefinitions.label: Checkpoint Configuration Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.removeCtrlChars
configDefinitions.description: Use only if required as it impacts reading performance
configDefinitions.label: Ignore Control Characters

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.compression
configDefinitions.description: Compression formats gzip, bzip2, xz, lzma, Pack200, DEFLATE and Z are supported. Archive formats 7z, ar, arj, cpio, dump, tar and zip are supported.
configDefinitions.label: Compression Format

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.filePatternInArchive
configDefinitions.description: A glob or regular expression that defines the pattern of the file names within the compressed directory.
configDefinitions.label: File Name Pattern within Compressed Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.textMaxLineLen
configDefinitions.description: Longer lines are truncated
configDefinitions.label: Max Line Length

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.jsonMaxObjectLen
configDefinitions.description: Larger objects are not processed
configDefinitions.label: Max Object Length (chars)

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.csvMaxObjectLen
configDefinitions.description: Larger objects are not processed
configDefinitions.label: Max Record Length (chars)

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.csvSkipStartLines
configDefinitions.description: Number of lines to skip before reading
configDefinitions.label: Lines to Skip

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.xmlRecordElement
configDefinitions.description: XML element that acts as a record delimiter. No delimiter will treat the whole XML document as one record.
configDefinitions.label: Delimiter Element

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.xmlMaxObjectLen
configDefinitions.description: Larger records are not processed
configDefinitions.label: Max Record Length (chars)

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.logMaxObjectLen
configDefinitions.description: Longer lines are truncated
configDefinitions.label: Max Line Length

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.retainOriginalLine
configDefinitions.description: Indicates if the original line of log should be retained in the record
configDefinitions.label: Retain Original Line

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.regex
configDefinitions.description: The regular expression which is used to parse the log line.
configDefinitions.label: Regular Expression

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.fieldPathsToGroupName
configDefinitions.description: Map groups in the regular expression to field paths
configDefinitions.label: Field Path To RegEx Group Mapping

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.grokPatternDefinition
configDefinitions.description: Define your own grok patterns which will be used to parse the logs
configDefinitions.label: Grok Pattern Definition

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.grokPattern
configDefinitions.description: The grok pattern which is used to parse the log line
configDefinitions.label: Grok Pattern

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.maxStackTraceLines
configDefinitions.description: Any line that does not match the expected pattern will be treated as a Stack trace as long as it is part of the same message. The stack trace will be trimmed to the specified number of lines.
configDefinitions.label: Trim Stack Trace to Length

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.log4jCustomLogFormat
configDefinitions.description: Specify your own custom log4j format.
configDefinitions.label: Custom Log4J Format

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.avroSchema
configDefinitions.description: Overrides the schema associated with the message. Optionally use the runtime:loadResource function to use a schema stored in a file
configDefinitions.label: Avro Schema

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.protoDescriptorFile
configDefinitions.description: Protobuf Descriptor File (.desc) path relative to SDC resources directory
configDefinitions.label: Protobuf Descriptor File

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.messageType
configDefinitions.description: Fully Qualified Message Type name. Use format <packageName>.<messageTypeName>
configDefinitions.label: Message Type

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.isDelimited
configDefinitions.description: Should be checked when the input data is prepended with the message size. When unchecked only a single message can be present in the source file/Kafka message, etc.
configDefinitions.label: Delimited Messages

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormatConfig.binaryMaxObjectLen
configDefinitions.description: Larger objects are not processed
configDefinitions.label: Max Data Size (bytes)

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataFormat
configDefinitions.description: Format of data in the files
configDefinitions.label: Data Format

configDefinitions.name: conf.spoolDir
configDefinitions.description: Use a local directory
configDefinitions.label: Files Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.allowLateDirectory
configDefinitions.description: Enables reading from a late-arriving directory. When enabled, the origin does not validate the configured path.
configDefinitions.label: Allow Late Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.overrunLimit
configDefinitions.description: Low level reader buffer limit to avoid out of Memory errors
configDefinitions.label: Buffer Limit (KB)

configDefinitions.name: conf.batchSize
configDefinitions.description: Max number of records per batch
configDefinitions.label: Batch Size (recs)

configDefinitions.name: conf.poolingTimeoutSecs
configDefinitions.description: Max time to wait for new files before sending an empty batch
configDefinitions.label: Batch Wait Time (secs)

configDefinitions.name: conf.filePattern
configDefinitions.description: A glob or regular expression that defines the pattern of the file names in the directory. Files are processed in lexicographically increasing order.
configDefinitions.label: File Name Pattern

configDefinitions.name: conf.maxSpoolFiles
configDefinitions.description: Max number of files in the directory waiting to be processed. Additional files cause the pipeline to fail.
configDefinitions.label: Max Files in Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.initialFileToProcess
configDefinitions.description: When configured, the Data Collector does not process earlier (naturally ascending order) file names
configDefinitions.label: First File to Process

configDefinitions.name: conf.errorArchiveDir
configDefinitions.description: Directory for files that could not be fully processed
configDefinitions.label: Error Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.postProcessing
configDefinitions.description: Action to take after processing a file
configDefinitions.label: File Post Processing

configDefinitions.name: conf.archiveDir
configDefinitions.description: Directory to archive files after they have been processed
configDefinitions.label: Archive Directory

configDefinitions.name: conf.retentionTimeMins
configDefinitions.description: How long archived files should be kept before deleting, a value of zero means forever
configDefinitions.label: Archive Retention Time (mins)

configDefinitions.name: stageOnRecordError
configDefinitions.description: Action to take with records sent to error
configDefinitions.label: On Record Error

configDefinitions.name: fileName
configDefinitions.description: The full path of the file
configDefinitions.label: File Path

stages.name: com_cisco_mazut_ss_destination_CopyToHDFSTarget
stages.description: Custom HDFS destination to store text files "as is", reads from /text record location
stages.label: Copy to HDFS Destination

configDefinitions.name: config
configDefinitions.label: Local directory with Hadoop config files

configDefinitions.name: stageOnRecordError
configDefinitions.description: Action to take with records sent to error
configDefinitions.label: On Record Error

configDefinitions.name: stageRequiredFields
configDefinitions.description: Records without any of these fields are sent to error
configDefinitions.label: Required Fields

configDefinitions.name: stageRecordPreconditions
configDefinitions.description: Records that don't satisfy all the preconditions are sent to error
configDefinitions.label: Preconditions
